raw_data.title: SME Consultant
raw_data.description:
Securityhunter Subject Matter Expert’s (SME) provide consulting services that support client’s ongoing security initiatives. Our consultants offer a thorough working knowledge of countermeasures including but not limited to physical access control (PACS), video surveillance (VSS), CCTV, intrusion detection (IDS), emergency communication solutions, cloud solutions, information technology, information assurance, information security, vulnerability assessments, emerging technologies, anti-terrorism technology and training, operational training, law enforcement technology, drone related technology and command and control systems. Our team of SMEs provides comprehensive reviews and assessments. The SME (Expert) evaluates and recommends the countermeasures that would most effectively resolve or mitigate outlined threats and vulnerabilities. Countermeasures will address risk avoidance, reduction, spreading and transference in addition to providing reasonable, cost effective and appropriate control measures that commensurate with the risks to which an organization is exposed. The full range of consulting services include: developing and analyzing vulnerability & risk assessment reports, generating statements of work for recommended security countermeasures, creating independent government cost estimates, conducting pre-bid walk through with contractors, providing contractor negotiation support, communication liaison between Contract Officer’s  Technical Representative (COTR) & Project Managers, facilitates audits and generates project test plan and commissioning documents, recommends existing and emerging technologies.
Minimum Experience: 8 years experience in a related field. Minimum Education Requirements: Bachelors Degree or a level of experience that commensurate with the rigors of an advanced degree.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Bachelors Degree equal to 8 years relevant experience.

labor_categories.years_experience: Bachelors Degree equal to 8 years relevant experience.

raw_data.title: Engineering Technician
raw_data.description: Electronic Engineering Technicians help design, develop, test, manufacture, and repair electrical and electronic equipment. Electronics engineering technicians generally work under the supervision of Sr. Field Engineer and Project Managers. Technicians perform a wide variety of different tasks depending on the needs of the project. Technicians will monitor control units to make sure that the electronic solution and systems are operating efficiently. He/She test and inspect equipment to verify that it meets the required specifications. They often use their knowledge of electrical engineering technology to diagnose electrical problems. They may make repairs themselves or direct other electrical workers to do them. They consult with engineers and offer advice on power and connectivity.  They may plan, direct, and record tests done on electrical equipment, or recommend changes in equipment that is not operating efficiently. Engineering technicians perform a variety of tasks to assist the engineers, such as assembling and testing experimental electrical and electronic parts or making changes in parts according to an engineer's instructions. They also prepare wiring diagrams, layout drawings, or engineering specifications for new equipment. Once a design for new equipment has been perfected, electrical and electronic engineering technicians may direct the crew of workers who produce or install it. Electronic Engineering Technician - Minimum Experience: 3-10 years experience in a related field. Minimum Education Requirements: High school diploma, technical training or a level of experience that commensurate with the rigors of a diploma.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: High School Diploma equal to Technical Training or 3 years experience.

labor_categories.years_experience: High School Diploma equal to Technical Training or 3 years experience.

raw_data.title: Help Desk Specialist I
raw_data.description: Help Desk Operators serve outside customers, assisting with a variety of functions related to computers and software. When customers experience technical difficulties, they contact help desk operators to answer questions and/or diagnoses technical and operational problems. Help desk operators provide step-by-step solutions to the caller. When computer hardware needs repair, operators pick up the computer or arrange for its transportation. If it cannot be fixed internally, the help desk operator arranges for repair from an outside service and ensures that the hardware is delivered. Help desk operators keep records of callers, the problem experienced, and the resolution. raw_data.title: Installation Technician I

Installs, maintains, and operates electronic security equipment. Implements system testing and preventive maintenance programs. Performs routine technical security integration functions related to the support of the development of security engineering activities such as set-up, operation, maintenance, modification, circuit testing, calibration and trouble shooting and repair of electronic or electro-mechanical systems, experimental design circuitry, prototype models or specialized test equipment. Works from the following: schematics, logic diagrams, written and verbal descriptions, layouts, and plans. Works independently to install, operate, maintain, troubleshoot and/or repair highly complex mechanical, electronic or integrated systems.
